[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## General Architecture Pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A healthcare clinical-trial recruitment bot decomposes into ten logical stages: candidate entry with channel-specific authentication and consent, longitudinal-store initialization (lighter than the chronic-disease and mental-health recipes because the relationship is shorter), input safety screening with continuous crisis screening (for serious-condition trial populations), trial portfolio matching with candidate characteristics, plain-language trial introduction grounded in IRB-approved materials, structured pre-screening with IRB-approved question sets, question-and-answer with IRB-approved-materials grounding, interest assessment with neutral framing, warm handoff to research coordinators (consent-gated where applicable), and audit logging with IRB-reporting discipline. The cross-cutting concerns from recipes 11.1 through 11.9 carry forward; this recipe adds five new ones (IRB-approved-materials-corpus governance with versioned-asset discipline, structured pre-screening pipeline as architectural primitive, balanced-presentation verification in output safety, equity-aware recruitment design with per-cohort monitoring as launch-gate, and FDA-strategy alignment for FDA-regulated investigations).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── CANDIDATE ENTRY + CHANNEL CONSENT ────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Candidate enters via one of several channels]         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Authenticated patient-portal (existing patient,     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      logged in, recruitment-conversation initiated by    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      care team or institutional outreach)                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Unauthenticated public (recruitment website,        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      registry-and-bot integration)                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Clinician-referral (link or code from treating      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      clinician)                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Study-team-direct (research coordinator invite)     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Per-channel authentication and consent]               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Authenticated channels: institution session         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      conveys verified patient_id and access scope        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Unauthenticated channels: minimal data collected    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      until candidate consents                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Channel-specific IRB-approved consent language      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Recruitment-specific consent for use of conversation│
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      data, retention scope, follow-up scope              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Disclosure and IRB-approval transparency]             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - "I'm a chat tool, not a person, and not a research  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      coordinator"                                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - "I help you learn about trials and run pre-screening│
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      questions; I do not sign you up and do not run the  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      formal consent process"                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - "This conversation is conducted under IRB approval  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      [number]; you can stop at any time"                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: session_id, channel, authentication context,  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    consent_id, IRB-approval reference]                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── LONGITUDINAL STORE INITIALIZATION ────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Candidate-bot store, lighter than chronic-disease     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    and mental-health recipes because relationship is     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    shorter]                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Candidate stated condition or interest area         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Stated demographic data (age, sex, language) with   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      appropriate consent for use                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Stated preferences (language, channel, contact      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      time, reading-level preference)                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Conversation history (typically short)              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Pre-screening responses with version-stamping       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Trial-engagement history (which trials presented,   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      which pre-screened, which interested)               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Consent posture (sharing scope, follow-up scope,    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      clinician-notification scope)                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Where authenticated: chart-context with consent     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      (active conditions, medications, recent encounters  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      for chart-screening confirmation)                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: candidate-recruitment store ready]            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── INPUT SAFETY + CRISIS SCREENING ──────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Standard input safety primitives from recipe 11.1]    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Prompt-injection detection                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - PHI minimization                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Crisis screening for serious-condition populations]   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Mental-health-trial candidates may disclose         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      suicidal ideation or self-harm thoughts; the bot    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      runs continuous crisis screening as in recipe 11.8  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Oncology-trial candidates may disclose acute        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      symptoms requiring clinical attention               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Pain-trial candidates may disclose acute pain       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      crises                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - The crisis-pathway response is deferred to the      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      institution's clinical-care infrastructure (e.g.,   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      988 for suicidal-ideation disclosures, the          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      candidate's care team for acute clinical symptoms,  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      911 for active emergencies); the trial-recruitment  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      bot does not absorb the crisis response as part of  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      its scope                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Sensitive-disclosure detection]                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - The candidate may disclose sensitive medical history│
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      during pre-screening; the response is to confirm    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      consent for the disclosure, capture only what is    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      needed for the pre-screening, and defer broader     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      conversations to the research coordinator           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: input passes / input blocked / crisis pathway │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    triggered with deferred routing]                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── TRIAL PORTFOLIO MATCHING ─────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Trial portfolio]                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active trials managed by the institution            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-trial metadata: condition, phase, intervention, │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      eligibility-criteria summary, IRB approval status,  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      target enrollment, current enrollment, recruitment  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      window, location, inclusion-and-exclusion criteria, │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      principal investigator, research coordinator(s),    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      IRB-approved candidate-facing materials version     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Candidate-trial matching]                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Filter by condition (candidate's stated condition)  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Filter by basic demographic eligibility (e.g., adult│
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      vs. pediatric, sex-specific, geographic)            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Filter by recruitment-window status (open vs. paused│
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      vs. closing)                                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Match-presentation: typically present 1-3 trials in │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      balanced fairness, with explicit framing            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Cross-trial fairness]                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - The bot does not steer toward sponsor-incentive or  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      easy-enrollment trials                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Trial-presentation policy is owned by institutional │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      research-operations and reviewed by IRB             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: matched-trial set for candidate engagement]   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── PLAIN-LANGUAGE TRIAL INTRODUCTION ────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Per-trial IRB-approved candidate-facing materials]    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Plain-language trial purpose                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Population the trial is studying                    │
