[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── AUDIT, IRB REPORTING, AND ANALYTICS ──────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Durable conversation record]                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - User utterances                                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool calls with arguments and results               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Generated bot responses                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active model and prompt versions                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active IRB-approved-materials version per trial     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active pre-screening question-set version per trial │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Final disposition (handoff, no-go, deferred)        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [IRB-specific retention and reporting]                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Retention sized to longest of HIPAA's six-year      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      minimum, the IRB's specified retention for          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      research-related records (often longer), the trial- │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      specific retention requirements, and any            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      litigation-hold obligations                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - IRB receives per-trial recruitment-conversation     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      summaries on the IRB's specified cadence            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - IRB receives adverse-event-style reports for        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      unexpected events                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Operational telemetry]                                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Engagement rate by trial                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Pre-screening completion rate                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Pre-screening outcome distribution                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Coordinator-handoff completion rate                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Time-to-first-coordinator-contact                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Coordinator-confirmed eligibility rate (the         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      coordinator's formal eligibility evaluation         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      compared with the bot's pre-screening outcome)      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Citation-coverage rate                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Balanced-presentation-violation rate                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-cohort metric slices (language, channel,        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      condition, age cohort, sex, race-ethnicity where    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      consented, geography, social-determinant flags)     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Equity metric: candidate-pool diversity vs. trial   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      target population vs. institution patient mix       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Sampled review]                                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Random sample plus targeted sample of complex       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      pre-screening outcomes, edge-case Q&A, and          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      candidate complaints                                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Reviewers (research operations and IRB-trained)     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      tag failure modes (out-of-scope, consent-process-   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      drift, balanced-presentation-violation, persuasion- │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      drift, citation-gap, scope-violation)               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Materials-corpus revisions driven by review with    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      IRB-approval gating                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: audit trail, telemetry, learning signals,     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    materials-revision proposals]                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the trial-recruitment bot.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **IRB-approved-materials-corpus governance with versioned-asset discipline.** The candidate-facing-materials library is owned by institutional research operations, version-controlled, IRB-approved-stamped, and updated only on IRB approval. Every response cites the version used.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Structured pre-screening pipeline as architectural primitive.** Pre-screening is conducted using IRB-approved structured question sets with explicit decision rules; the pre-screening produces a non-binding outcome; formal eligibility is the research coordinator's job.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Balanced-presentation discipline as architectural primitive.** Recruitment communication presents risks and benefits, experimental and control, the trial and alternatives, in balanced terms. The system prompt, the IRB-approved materials, and the output-safety review enforce balance.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Consent-process scope exclusion as architectural primitive.** The bot does not perform informed consent. Consent-process drift is detected and rejected by output safety.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-trial governance with IRB-approval lifecycle.** Each trial in the portfolio has IRB-approved materials, IRB-approved pre-screening questions, IRB-approved consent posture, named research coordinators, and a managed lifecycle (open, accruing, amended, closing).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Equity-aware recruitment design with per-cohort monitoring as launch-gate.** Engagement, pre-screening, and handoff metrics are monitored per-cohort with explicit equity focus.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Coordinator-handoff infrastructure with workforce capacity sizing.** Research-coordinator capacity is sized to expected handoff volume, with peak-hour and per-trial coverage.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **FDA-strategy alignment for FDA-regulated investigations.** Where the trial is FDA-regulated, recruitment communication is subject to FDA advertising guidance; the institutional regulatory team is involved in materials-corpus review.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Citation discipline as architectural primitive.** Every recruitment-communication assertion is grounded in a cited IRB-approved source with version preserved.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Conservative-bias-default policy.** When the bot is uncertain about content, when candidate questions go beyond IRB-approved materials, when the conversation drifts toward consent or enrollment commitment, the response defaults to "let me connect you with a research coordinator."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Engagement, pre-screening, handoff, citation-coverage, balanced-presentation, and equity metrics are monitored per language, channel, condition, age cohort, sex, race-ethnicity (where consented), geography, and social-determinant flags.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When the materials store, the pre-screening question store, the coordinator-handoff queue, or any escalation pathway is unreachable, the bot degrades gracefully. The minimum behavior is "I'm having trouble right now; please contact our research coordinator at [phone or email] for trial information" with direct routing to coordinator contact.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
